This paper deals with query processing in distributed computational environments, specifically in the context of MapReduce. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the database (cs.DB), distributed computing (cs.DC), and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses optimization techniques for communication cost, which is a common concern in machine learning (cs.LG) and data mining (cs.DM) research.
